Description: Main System for any cinematic needs

Name: Primary Skills
Description:
Skills To be Acquired by interacting with %15 
Skills are enumerated in Enum for Reference in code.

Name: Interactables
Description: Any Object that the player can interact via button press, attacking.

Name: Skill Shrine
Description:
**Type:** %82 

Contains one %13 for the %9 to unlock
Shows %62 after acquiring it

Name: Combat
Description:
Combat Happens when the %21 of a %18 touches the %20 of %19.

### **RULES**
-All attack instance should only have 1 %22 
-Damageable can resist different %22 at different percentages
-Flinching is occurs when certain conditions are met

Name: Damage Calculation
Description:
The Following will occur
1. Based on Critical Chance: Increase the Damage of %18
2. Reduce the Damage based on %23 for each Damage Type
3. Apply Each Damage to %19

Name: Attacker
Description:
The Component needed to deal Damage 
Needs %21 for it to be fully functional.

Contains:
- Damage Value
- Damage Modifier
- Critical Chance
- Ignore Certain %25

Name: Damageable
Description:
The component that indicates this object can be damage
%20 is needed to be fully functional

Contains
- Reference to Health
- Reference to %23

Name: Hitbox
Description:
Signifies which Collider is needed to be hit for the %19 to take damage

Contains:
%25

Name: Collider Damage
Description: Signifies which Colliders deal damage when it collides with a %20

Name: Damage Type
Description:
Damage can be one of the Following (Enums):
- TRUE (for the purpose of bypassing)
- Physical
- Fire
- Poison

Name: Damage Resistance
Description: Reduces the value of a damage type when received

Name: Status Effect
Description:
Status are abnormalities that are inflicted to the player or to the enemies. When the player is inflicted with a status effect, the effect occurs for a duration of time or when it is cured.

While still inflicted by the status effect, the duration will reset if the player receives the same status effect.

Name: Invulnerability Level
Description: Level based where in %19 can be invulnerable to %18 if Damageable's Invul Level is higher than Attacker's Ignore Invul Level

Name: Cinemachine
Description: A Plugin from Unity that will govern majority of the Cinematic

Name: Camera Area
Description:
Contains a %29 with its own settings.
When %9's %20 enters its trigger area, the %29 is enabled.
When %9 leaves the area, it will ask %30 for a resolution

Name: Main Camera
Description:
The one camera that renders object in scene
Has a Component called CinemachineBrain for it to work with %29

Name: Virtual Camera
Description:
Cinemachine's Camera Object which contains information and behavior for the %28 to follow.
%28 only follows the latest enabled Virtual Camera

Name: Cinema
Description: Handles All of Cinematic Needs

Description:

Name: Zone Serialization
Description: Saving State of Various Objects that are exclusive in the scene

Name: Zone Data Handle
Description:
Handles the Serialization of a Zone
Needs References to %37  objects

Deserializes and Updates all Referenced %37 when zone is loaded.
Listens to %38 Events

Name: Component Serializer
Description:
**Requires a Component with ISerializableComponent Interface to work**
A medium for Serializing and Deserializing Components
It has its own ID for security and matching purposes when Serializing and Deserializing

Name: Serializer
Description:
Handles All the Serialization and Deserialization of all Objects in the Gameplay.

Has Pre-Serialization and Post-Deserialization Events

Name: Object Pooling
Description:
Pools Object for recycling instances.

Has Different Global Pools for specific objects

Name: Gameplay System
Description: A, Object instance for All World Objects to go to in order to interact with the Games system

Name: Gameplay UI Handle
Description: Contains All Functions that Shows UI Stuff

Name: DoozyUI
Description: A Plugin used for All UI Management needs

Name: Dialogue System
Description: A Plugin used for all Dialogue and Questing Needs

Name: Spine Unity
Description: A Plugin to integrate Spine Outputs to Unity

Name: Player Manager
Description:
Links %9 to the System
Allows Direct Changes and References to %9 Character.

Name: Player Character
Description:
The in Game representation of the player 

[PLAYER MOVEMENT LIST AND CONTROLS](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1SzcfvEhtHg1fceegI9b6dYUrbwLYBkSOfrkY4WMW2Pk/edit)

Name: Player Logic
Description:
Contains all data that the player has but may not be directly showed to his %46 

Applies the Data to %46 upon deserialization and Awake

Contains::
- Its own %49

Name: Character Controller
Description: [PLAYER CONTROLS](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1SzcfvEhtHg1fceegI9b6dYUrbwLYBkSOfrkY4WMW2Pk/edit?usp=sharing)

Name: Inventory
Description: Allows Characters to carry a number of Items

Name: Bestiary Tracking
Description:
Contains IDs of %52 it has already encountered.
Records Bestiary Data When it killed the enemy for the first time and notifies the player via %63 .
Is Connected to Player's %18 for First Killed Record.

Name: Bestiary Data
Description:
Data for Creatures Encountered and Killed
Contains the Following:
- ID
- Name
- Title
- Image
- Index Image
- Sketch Image
- Description
- Locations Its Located in

Name: Player Progression
Description: Anything that has something to do with Player Progression

Name: Bestiary
Description:
Datas are created in the form of %52, which is then tracked by %50.
Information Tracked by %50 is shown in %59 .

Name: Store
Description: A Book thing of some sort that serves as a sub menu for the player during gameplay

Name: Bestiary Tab
Description: Shows %52 recorded by %50 either in a list or detailed information.

Name: Primary Skill Data
Description:
Contains Information of Primary Skill
- Name
- Description
- Skill Reference (Enum)
- Icon 
- Notification Border

Name: Notifications
Description:
Anything that notifies the Player via UI.
Player usually have to press a button to exit notification

Name: Primary Skill Notification
Description: Shows Information of newly acquired %13 using the %60 as basis

Name: Bestiary Update Notification
Description: Informs the Player that the %57 is Updated

Name: Item Data
Description:
An Class that signifies what an item is.
Contains the following
- ID
- Name
- Category
- Icon
- Quantity Limit
- Cost
- Description
- Can Be Sold

Name: Consumable Item Data
Description:
An Abstract Class that signifies an item that can be consumed.
Contains the following
- Data from %64
- Has Infinite Uses
- Abstract Function for if It can be used
- Abstract Function for when used

Name: Throwable Item Data
Description:
An Abstract Class that signifies an item is thrown when consumed.
Contains the following
- Data from %65 
- Instance of the item when consumed

Name: Usable Item Data
Description:
An Abstract Class that signifies an item that can be consumed.
Contains the following
- Data from %65
- Conditions for when An Item can be used.
- Effects that instantly occurs when consumed.
- If It has a Duration Effect, and what the duration is
- Effects that are active during the duration
- Effects that are updated during duration

Name: Item Slot
Description: Contains %64 and the number of instances it has in the slot.

Name: Item Container
Description:
Representation of a Character's Inventory.
Contains a List of %68.
Items can be modified via the Item Container

Name: Trading
Description: Allows the exchange of items between two parties (usually a %72 and a %9)

Name: Friendlies
Description: NPCs that do not attack the Player unless a narrative event says otherwise

Name: Merchant
Description: A Character that Sells %73 to %9 via %70

Name: Items
Description: Available Items in game, made possible with %49

Name: Trading UI
Description:
A UI that shows the items of %72 to be traded when the Buy option selected or the items of %9 when the Sell Option is Selected.

It has a filter limit what items are shown based on Item Category

Name: Small Healing Potion
Description: Detailed Document - [Consumable Items Document](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TfmIxj4V_hsqNtOUQwrNmo0NkotvAAPnoOHnGP4t2ZQ/edit#heading=h.q0yqnabugyo5)

Name: Soul Essence
Description: Currency usually for %70.

Name: Loot
Description: Objects in Game that can be picked up by the %9 by going near it, It is then stored in the their %69 . Contains %64 to represent that item

Name: Loot Drop
Description: Certain ingame objects drops %77 (Variety and amount are either randomized or determined from a set)

Name: Loot Data
Description:
Data needed to drop a certain amount of %77. Requests %80 to spawn the loot

Has different type of Containers inside that determines what loot and their amount should be dropped. Each container can reference other containers for a flexible drop table

- Individual Loot (If only 1 type of %77 is needed to drop)
- Loot List (All Items in this is is dropped)
- Loot Drop (Items in this list has a chance to be dropped)

Name: Loot Drop Handle
Description:
Handles the Spawning of %77  in the Game World.
Spawns a max number per frame

Name: Object Interaction
Description: %9 is allowed to interact with %14.

Name: Button To Interact
Description: When Selected by %84 a button prompt is shown When the state `showPrompt` is true.

Name: Hit To Interact
Description: Player can hit the %14 to interact with it

Name: Interactable Detector
Description: This is an area where the player can interact with the closest %82 it will then show a prompt based on its state

Name: Breakables
Description: Objects that are attacked to be destroyed. State can be Serialized if wanted

Name: Obstacles
Description:
Objects that is able to damage player but can be destroyed or just straight out hinders

[OBSTACLES LIST](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JvgymnKT6RW41jsMgMgDhWJK1RExyvYin3oWNUhRnoY/edit?usp=sharing)

Name: NPC Dialogue
Description: A %82 NPC that starts of a dialogue

Name: Basic Behaviour
Description: Behaviours %9 has right out of the box

Name: Crouch
Description:
Player crouches making his collider smaller when the button is held.
They should not stand automatically when the button is released IF the environment doesn't allow them to stand properly
%90 while crouching changes the speed

Name: Jump
Description: Holding the Jump Button allows for maximum Jump height. Releasing it early stop the jump early

Name: Auto Step
Description: Terrain might have small inclination in height so this should automatically move the player onto that terrain without the need of jumping. Due to Unity's collision moving towards such terrain does not automatically to that

Name: Slash Attack
Description:
Basic Attack of the Player, Attacks should not register when environment is in the way
A Slash Attack that has a change in behavior depending on stance:
- Standing on Ground allows a combo slash attack
- Standing while %94 allows an up slash attack.
- %89 allows a forward slash attack
- Midair Allows a forward slash attack
- Midair while %94  allows a up slash attack

Name: Double Jump
Description: Allows another 1 Jump while mid-Air. This resets when you land on ground or %100

Name: Dash
Description:
A burst of speed moving in 1 direction.
Can be interrupted when damage or when %91 or %95 occurs mid-dash.

Name: Shadow Gauge
Description: A source of Energy for Shadow Abilities

Name: Shadow Skills
Description: Skills that uses a certain amount %97 and can by pass some environment

Name: Shadow Dash
Description: %96 with the benefit of %98. If there is no available amount of %97 use %96 instead

Name: Wall Movement
Description: Can Stick to wall but gradually slides down, when there is no wall to stick to as they slide, cancel Wall Stick. Allow Movement up the wall, when there is no wall to move up to attempt %101 when Up Button is Inputted. Player can also Jump From the Wall when Jump Button is Inputted.

Name: Ledge Grab
Description: When Player is in midair near an edge of a platform and still motions towards the platform, they will automatically climb up after a few checks that indicate that there's space to climb up to and that its safe

Name: Whip Attack
Description:
A longer ranged but weaker attack, Attacks should register when it passes through certain environment
A Whip Attack that has a change in behavior depending on stance:
- Standing on Ground allows a Whip attack
- Standing while %94 allows an up Whip attack.
- %89 allows a forward Whip attack
- Midair Allows a forward Whip attack
- Midair while %94  allows a up Whip attack

Name: Devil Wings
Description:
%9 Sprouts wings and is able to maintain Y-axis as they move in the X-axis while holding the button. This constantly consumes %97 while activated. 

This Deactivates automatically when the player uses the following:
- %96 
- %99 
- %102 
- %93

Name: Shadow Slide
Description: Similar to %96 but the player sinks into the ground making its collider even smaller in order to fit through small spaces. This doesn't end unless player is able to stand up

Name: Sword Thrust
Description:
A Charge Sword Attack
Holding the Slash Button for a certain amount of time unleashes this attack.
Attack deals greater Damage and can destroy certain environment.

Name: Earth Shaker
Description:
Can Only be done Mid Air.
Pressing the Down Button and Holding the Slash Button unleashes this attack.
Player Falls down at a great speed, damaging enemies as in the way.
when the player hits the ground they deal more damage to their surroundings and ends the Earth Shaker.
This can destroy certain environment

Name: IFrames
Description: When Damaged the Player is knockback and loses input control temporarily but also gains Max %25 for a short time

Name: Shadow Morph
Description:
Player Engulfs itself in shadow able to move through certain environment. Then you gain Max %25.
This constantly consumes %97.

This Disables the Following:
- %96 
- %91 
- %95 
- %104 
- %103 
- %99 
- %100

Name: Black Blood Immunity
Description: Player is Immune to Black Blood Damage

Name: Skull Throw
Description: Player Acquires <insert Item> to throw infinitely

Name: Throw Projectiles
Description:
Able to Aim and throw %66.
Press and Hold while moving directional buttons to aim
release to throw.

Is cancelled when Damaged.

When Canceled throw automatically.

Name: Throwable Skull
Description:
**Type:** %66 

**Description:** Player's Skull, that can be thrown infinitely

Name: Ghost Haunting Mechanic
Description: A certain closed door can only be opened when the player has killed %126. Player has to look for haunting ghost all over that location, once found they can injure it until its "dead". It will just teleport and reappear in a different Zone and Position. There will be an indicator near the door to show where the ghost might be and if its almost close to dying.

Name: Status Effect Reciever
Description: A component that enables the Character to be afflicted with Status Effects

Name: Status Inflictor
Description: Has a List of Status Effect and their chance of afflicting target.

Name: Status Resistance
Description: Has a List of Status Effect and a value to resist the status that its being inflicted with

Name: Bleeding [REMOVED]
Description:
### **Description:**
- This status damages the entity whenever they try to move or attack.
- All shadow skills will just pause the bleeding. The status duration will continue to take its effect upon returning to normal form.

### **Stats:**
- [DPS, Duration, Curable] - deals True damage over time
- Damage value: 20
- Damage interval: when performing movement or attack actions
- Duration: 30 seconds

### **Cure:**
- %238 
- The player can stop the effect by holding the down button but the duration does not decrease. Pressing other buttons such as walking, jumping and attack action will resume the bleeding effect. If it is held for 5 seconds, the bleeding will be cured.

### **REMOVED AS OF MARCH 15, 2022**
- Approved by Martin Ebido

Name: Burning
Description:
### **Description:**
- This status stops the player from using any shadow abilities and from generating or regenerating shadow for the duration of the status. For visual queue the Shadow Gauge/Bar in the player UI will stop generating/regenerating.

### **Stats:**
- [DPS, Duration] - deals **FIRE** damage over time.
- Damage value: 20
- Damage interval: 2 seconds
- Duration: 20 seconds
- This status effect will temporarily disable the shadow gauge/bar usage for 20 seconds.

### **Cure:**
- Frost Rune Crystal (consumable)
- %238 
- Mystic Water (Subject to change)
- %244 
- Water Buckets (Breakable Objects)
- Normal Dashing 5 times (Subject to change)

Name: Imp
Description:
This is a mischievous little demon that is making fun with its victim by making objects disappear and reappear but this behavior only works on the realm of nightmare. It can also set up barrel bomb as a trap then explodes when the proximity sensor is triggered.

IMP 
---

##### STATS RATING: (1-10)

Health     : 2
Damage     : 5 (this is for barrel bomb damage only)
Difficulty : 6 (due to its invisibility behavior)

---
### **BEHAVIOR:**


##### PATROL:
1.	When player is not detected move between two designated points.

##### DETECT PLAYER:
1.	Play detection animation to cue that it saw the player.
2.	Its player-sensor would be 4.5CH or 4.5 Character Height. (_4.5CH in front and 4.5CH in its back_)
a.	Overall sensor dimension is 9CH (Width) x 4CH (Height) and the imp will be placed at the center.
3.	Play detection animation if attacked even if the player is outside its detection range then play despawn.

##### ATTACK: (Other location)
1.	After the detection animation, play regurgitate-bomb animation.
2.	Play the despawn animation if the barrel bomb was already set in place.
3.	If the player attacks the barrel bomb during the regurgitation animation, trigger explosion effects (sound and visuals) and play knock-back animation then despawn.
4.	If the bomb explosion successfully hits the player, trigger the Imps laughing sound #1.
5.	~~(Can regurgitate bomb even if it in its invisible state?????)~~

##### DESPAWN TO INVISIBLE MODE:
1.	After the bomb placement, play despawn animation and trigger the Imps laughing sound #1. 
2.	Turn-off the IMPs hurtbox when it is in its invisible state.

##### RESPAWN TO VISIBLE MODE:
1.	When player is not detected for 3 to 5min, play respawn animation and trigger the laughing sound #2.
2.	It will remain invisible if it still detects the player.

##### DEATH:
1.	Play death animation if killed and trigger the laughing sound #3.
Respawn from Death:
1.	1 min after its death, play respawn animation and trigger the laughing sound #2. (use the same animation as the respawn to visible mode)

##### SOUND CUE:
1.	The laughing sound of despawn and successful bomb damage to player will trigger the laughing sound #1. (a cute but super evil laugh).
2.	The laughing sound of respawn to visible mode and respawn from death will trigger the laughing sound #2 (a cute but super evil laugh or we can also use a woohoow or yahoo sound).
3.	The laughing sound of the Imps death will trigger the laughing sound #3 (a suffering but still has a cute and super evil laugh).

---

#### **IMP'S SPECIAL BEHAVIOR:** (Realm of Nightmare only)
1.	The disappearance and reappearance of pre-determined platforms and walls are part of the Realm of Nightmares game mechanics that reacts to the players jump animation and we will just use the Imp minions as if they are the one causing this trickery.
2.	The disappearance and reappearance of platforms and walls will randomly trigger the Imps laughing sound as if it is still around making fun with the player.
3.	According to Sir Hai, we will only show the Imps despawn animation once something like an in-game cinematics then we will not show its physical form to the player ever again. We will just randomly trigger the Imps laughing sound when the platform and walls disappears and reappears.
4.	We will not use Bomber Imp animation in the realm of the nightmare.

**In Phase 1** %154 has the following attacks.
- Chain Fist
- Shoulder Bash
- Leap Attack 3x

When %154 's HP hits 90% of max HP or below. He Transitions to Phase 2 and does a Phase Discharge attack.

**In Phase 2** %154 has the following attacks.
- Chain Fist
- Shoulder Bash
- Chained Shoulder Bash
- Leap Attack 3x
- Leap Attack 6x

When %154 's HP hits 60% of max HP or below. He transitions to Phase 3 and does a Phase Discharge attack.

**In Phase 3** %154 has the following attacks.
- Chain Fist
- Shoulder Bash
- Chained Shoulder Bash
- Chain Shock
- Lightning Stomp
- Leap Attack 3x
- Leap Attack 6x

After defeating %154 the %167 [**2_SD_4**] and %260 [**2_DG_6**] opens.

It is a spherical crystal blessed with magical abilities and enhancements. The crystals can be acquired after defeating or slaying an enemy Boss and it can only be activated using the ancient stone relic.

All Soul Skills can only be assigned to one specific Soul Slot. Once an empty slot had been chosen, the inventory box will appear and displays the soul skills (acquired) to be assigned.

Types of Souls Skills:
- Blessed Crystals - are soul crystal orbs inside the body of an enemy boss. These orbs can be acquired after defeating an enemy then unlocks its active skills/abilities for the next user.
- Cursed Crystals - are soul crystal orbs with trapped enemy boss inside it. These orbs can be acquired easily from the merchant, hidden rooms and puzzle rewards but the skills/abilities are inactive and can be activated after defeating the enemy inside it.

Name: Town Gate
Description:
The %450 will be off or deactivated at the start.

At first interaction, When the Player moves nearer to the %450 it will show an Icon (W icon) as a visual cue to the Player. The Player will use %76 to activate the %450.

At second interaction, The W icon will be shown again and when the player interacts with the %450 , the player will be teleported to the overworld map(Isometric Camera view).

Name: HP Shard
Description:
Collecting 3 HP Shards upgrades the player's health by 25.

When receiving or picking up a third HP Shard, the player will automatically consume all 3 Shards that are available and increases the player's health by 25.

Name: Shadow Shard
Description:
Collecting 2 Shadow Shards upgrades the player's Shadow Gauge by 25.

When receiving or picking up a second Shadow Shard, the player will automatically consume all 2 Shadow Shards that are available and increases the player's Shadow by 25.

Name: Loot Chest
Description:
Has different types of Chests that contains items such as Consumables, Quest Items, Souls Skills, Soul Essence, and Shards. These items can be collected by the player once opened. Once opened, it will stay open whenever the player re-enters the scene.

Types of Chest:
- Normal Chest
- Shadow Shard Chest
- HP Shard Chest
- Attack Shard Chest
- Souls Skills Chest
